"'''Bane of the Sith'''" is a short story by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] originally published in [[Star Wars Gamer 3|''Star Wars Gamer'' #3]], and since released on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]]. It concerns the events surrounding [[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane's]] life shortly after those depicted in ''[[Star Wars: Jedi vs. Sith]]'' and ''[[Darth Bane: Path of Destruction]]''. ''Bane of the Sith'' served as Anderson's final contribution to [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]].

==Plot summary==
[[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane]] travels in [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] in his ship, the ''[[Valcyn/Legends|Valcyn]]''. Bane is the lone survivor of the [[Seventh Battle of Ruusan|Battle of Ruusan]], in which Lord [[Skere Kaan]]'s [[thought bomb]] destroyed the entire [[Brotherhood of Darkness/Legends|Brotherhood of Darkness]] and most of the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] on the [[Ruusan/Legends|planet]]. Bane is accompanied in his journey by the unwelcome ghostly avatar of Lord [[Qordis]], one of the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] who perished in the battle.

Qordis chides Darth Bane for abandoning the Sith, while Darth Bane is concerned about carrying on the Sith legacy. As Darth Bane approaches [[Dxun/Legends|Dxun]], the beast moon of [[Onderon/Legends|Onderon]], the spirit of Qordis shuts down all of the ''Valcyn''{{'s}} systems. The ship crashes, but Bane survives through his use of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]].

As Bane sets out through the Dxun jungle, the spirit of Qordis causes the remains of the ''Valcyn'' to explode. Bane continues through the jungle, slaying a jungle creature and then encountering the spirit of Lord Kaan. Bane follows Lord Kaan until he reaches the pyramidal tomb of [[Freedon Nadd]]. Kaan leads Bane to a room inside the tomb that contains a [[Sith holocron/Legends|Sith holocron]] full of all the Sith knowledge Bane will need.

As Bane enters the room, barnacle-like symbiotes called [[orbalisk]]s fall from the ceiling and agonizingly affix themselves to Darth Bane's body. Darth Bane suppresses the pain and immerses himself in the knowledge found in the Sith holocron. Much later (probably days), Darth Bane emerges from the tomb invigorated with dark-side knowledge and power. He decides to revive the Sith, but using the [[Rule of Two/Legends|Rule of Two]]. Bane bends a flying beast to his will and mounts it, intending to travel to Onderon in search of an apprentice.

==Continuity==
''Bane of the Sith'' has inconsistencies with the ''[[Star Wars: Jedi vs. Sith]]'' comic and ''[[Darth Bane: Path of Destruction]]'' book, such as Darth Bane telling Kaan not to use the thought bomb, the timing of Bane's search for an apprentice, the timing of when Darth Bane adopts the Rule of Two and the manner in which Qordis dies on Ruusan.

==Legacy==
The short story is retold as part of ''[[Darth Bane: Rule of Two]]''.

